      <description>An idea zajeer may like -- Give the follow two options for raid level charm augs:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1) Have charm flags added to normal raid level augs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2) Create a quest similar to BiC to make the best charm aug.&amp;nbsp; Have it be considerably powerful after the last groupable/mini raid stage, but require parts from high end raids to take it to the point where it's better than the augs you normally get from raids. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Example:&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Quested up to mini raid level (comparable step 10 bic) - 125 hp mana&amp;nbsp; 2% spell&amp;nbsp; shield / dot shield&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Raid aug (non-quest) -&amp;nbsp; 175 hp mana 3% spell shield / dot shield&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Fully powered quested aug (multiple items from high end raids needed) - 225 hp mana 4% spell shield / dot shield&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This way any raider, regardless of out-of-raid playtime, can have access to raid level charm augs.&amp;nbsp; But raiders who are willing to put in effort outside of raids can get something that's a step above.&amp;nbsp; This also gives non-high end raiders a shot at a considerable upgrade, if they're willing to put the effort into it.&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
